args: Aaaah ha ha! Yes! With the power of the\nseed at my fingertips, I am invincible!
I'm going to have to shapeshift...\nMidgardsormr, lend me your power!
How long have I waited for this moment!
By absorbing you in dragon form,\nI will obtain even greater power.\nNow...become my strength!
I...can't break free... At this rate...
Leave those people be, Yurius,\nand face ME if you dare!
No! You weren't supposed to get here\nbefore I finished off the prince!
Ah, but my master saw through your\nlittle scheme and prepared for this.\nHe had me lead Albert here personally.
I stand by my assessment of your naiveté,\nbut underestimated your intelligence.\nStill, your efforts are for naught!
Now all of you may watch as the hero's\nbeloved friend perishes! Aaah ha ha ha!
What has gotten into you, Yurius?!\nWhy do you thirst for power so?!
It's hardly surprising that one who has\nalways been strong would fail to\nunderstand the futility of being weak.
Not that I WANT you to understand my\nfeelings—I've had enough of hypocrites\npretending to be my friend!
The fortunate often feel compelled to show\npity to those less so—and I was a fool\nto ever interpret that as friendship!
But I'll not make the same mistake again.\nAnd since you seem so determined to\nprotect your new, REAL friends...
World Ark! Release the true power\nof the seed of the abyss!
This is the true power that was hidden\nin the seed of the abyss—and it is\nalso the end for all of you!
Oh, but this is wonderful! You all made\nme out to be a fool, but look who is\nwrithing on the ground now!

Ah, but I am a merciful man who wouldn't
want any of you to be alone as you lament
for an eternity inside me...so I will absorb
the lot of you together!
He's lost control of his power...\nThat seed is going to consume him!
But he was controlling it perfectly\nuntil a few moments ago!
I have a feeling the device Phares gave\nhim was incomplete. There's likely a limit\nto how much power it can handle.

If we don't do something, his will is
going to be completely consumed,
and we'll have another tragedy like
Levin on our hands.
Damn it! Do as I command,\nyou useless dragon!
I refuse to let my life end like this!\nI was to be a king! A true king!
I cannot stand by and allow the\ntragedy of Levin to be repeated.
It seems my dream to save you and\ndestroy the seed was the dream of\na fool, old friend.
Killing you now is the only way\nto avert an even greater tragedy.
You still want to save your friend,\nand I believe that you can!
So if you really want to save him,\nreach out now with your voice!\nSpeak to him as his friend!
...You're right. I have to at least try.
No matter how insurmountable the odds,\nI will not let it be said I did not try\neverything possible to save him!
I will destroy the seed—and only the seed!\nHold on, Yurius! Just a bit longer!

Aaah ha ha! Madness! Utter madness!
My body and the seed are one and the
same—you cannot destroy one without
annihilating the other!
How loathsome you are, hero!\nEven when faced with a monster,\nyou must flaunt your compassion!
You came here to kill me,\nso do it already, if you can!
No! I am going to save you!
I am long past being able to believe your\nwords—I trust only my own strength now!
So if you insist on continuing this\nsanctimony, then behold!

The seed you seek is now one with my
my own heart. Go ahead and plunge your
sword into it—but don't expect me to let
go of you!
You can die an idealist, or push my hand\naside and live! Choose one! Aaaah ha ha!
This ends now! Die, you self-righteous fool!
If Albert didn't get away in time...
